message.content:
Analysis of the Target Structure:

• TOTAL BLOCKS & LAYERS  
  – The tower uses 8 total blocks arranged in 5 “layers” from bottom to top.  
  – Layer 1 (bottom): 1 long yellow rectangular block.  
  – Layer 2: 2 tall orange cylinders side by side.  
  – Layer 3: 1 yellow rectangular block bridging across the two cylinders.  
  – Layer 4: 2 blue cubes (centered) with a red arch spanning front‐to‐back just behind them.  
  – Layer 5 (top): 1 red “roof” block resting above the arch.

• SPATIAL RELATIONSHIPS  
  – The two orange columns stand on the yellow base and support the second yellow plank.  
  – The blue cubes sit on that yellow plank, and the red arch straddles those cubes.  
  – The red roof piece caps the entire structure on top of the arch.

Selecting Matching Blocks from the Dictionary:

1) Yellow rectangular blocks:  
   – Use block #7 (flat, horizontal yellow rectangle) twice.  
2) Orange cylinders (vertical):  
   – Use block #10 (orange cylinder standing upright) twice.  
3) Blue cubes:  
   – Use block #5 (blue cube) twice.  
4) Red arch (opening front‐to‐back):  
   – Use block #3.  
5) Red roof piece:  
   – Use block #12.

Hence, the required dictionary indices are: {7, 7, 10, 10, 5, 5, 3, 12}.

Assembly Order:
{
  Step1: Move block with index 7  
  Step2: Move block with index 10  
  Step3: Move block with index 10  
  Step4: Move block with index 7  
  Step5: Move block with index 5  
  Step6: Move block with index 5  
  Step7: Move block with index 3  
  Step8: Move block with index 12  
}
